  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Delivery Driver",
  "description": "<p>Pharmatech Medical Enterprise Pte Ltd - Where Innovation and Excellence Unite in Pharmaceutical Distribution</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Collect orders from the warehouse and verify their condition and completeness against invoices, order forms, and sample chits to ensure accuracy.</li><li>Plan optimal delivery routes using GPS or other navigation tools to maximize efficiency.</li><li>Deliver orders to clinics and hospitals on schedule, maintaining an organized travel itinerary.</li><li>Inspect the delivery vehicle daily to identify and report any malfunctions or damages for safety compliance.</li><li>Assist with loading and unloading items to ensure secure handling during transport.</li><li>Communicate professionally with customers to address complaints or concerns and maintain positive relationships.</li><li>Document each delivery by obtaining signatures or confirmations to verify receipt.</li><li>Process payments for deliveries when applicable, ensuring accurate transaction handling.</li><li>Adhere to traffic laws and practice safe driving at all times to ensure safety.</li><li>Help pack and check new orders for the next day’s delivery to maintain workflow continuity.</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Possess a valid Singapore driving license.</li><li>Demonstrate physical and mental fitness to perform delivery and vehicle handling tasks safely.</li><li>Apply knowledge of navigation and route planning to execute timely deliveries.</li><li>Maintain basic vehicle knowledge to support daily vehicle inspections.</li><li>Exhibit focus and patience to manage delivery schedules and customer interactions effectively.</li></ul>",
